    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n9563" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαλεπός</span></b> , comp. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαλεπώτερος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">hard, difficult,
            dangerous</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἄεθλος; λιμήν</span>,
          ‘hard to approach,’ <i><span class="en">Od. 11.622</span></i>, <i><span class="en">Od. 19.189</span></i>; personal const. w. inf.,
            <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαλεπή τοι ἐγὼ μένος ἀντιφέρεσθαι,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 21.482</span></i>; <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">
            χαλεποὶ θεοὶ ἐναργεῖς φαίνεσθαι</span>, ‘it is dangerous when
          gods appear, etc.’, <i><span class="en">Il. 20.131</span></i>;
          oftener the impers. const. Of things, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">harsh, grievous,
            severe;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">γῆρας, μόχθος, ὀνείδη, ἔπεα</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 23.489</span></i>; of persons, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">stern,
            angry</span>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">τινί</span>, <i><span class="en">Od. 17.388</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
